-- Balkan Bourses to Ease Regional Cooperation, Investors’ Access
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-03-27T08:03:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/balkan-bourses-to-ease-regional-cooperation-investors-access.html
Stock exchange representatives from
Zagreb, Belgrade, Ljubljana, Podgorica, Sarajevo, Skopje and
Tirana are expected to sign a cooperation agreement in Sarajevo,
Bosnia-Herzegovina.  The agreement, to be signed today, is designed to ease
investors’ access to regional markets, the  Zagreb stock exchange 
said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  